HEADWORD: Suscitate
<hw>Sus"ci*tate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Suscitated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Suscitating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>suscitatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>suscitare</ets> to lift up, to
rouse; pref. <ets>sus-</ets> (see <er>Sub-</er>) + <ets>citare</ets> to
rouse, excite. Cf. <er>Excite</er>, <er>Incite</er>.]</ety> <def>To
rouse; to excite; to call into life and action.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

